Leuthold Group LLC Continues to Hold Stake in Norfolk Southern Corp. (NSC)

July 19, 2017 - By Stephen Andrade

Investors sentiment decreased to 0.81 in 2016 Q4. Its down 0.09, from 0.9 in 2016Q3. It dived, as 54 investors sold NSC shares while 354 reduced holdings. 87 funds opened positions while 242 raised stakes. 197.51 million shares or 1.15% more from 195.27 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Bowen Hanes And reported 0.03% of its portfolio in Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC). Ig Invest accumulated 5,500 shares or 0% of the stock. 5,905 are owned by Ingalls Snyder Ltd Llc. Mercer Capital Advisers invested 0.64% in Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC). Jpmorgan Chase & Co, a New York-based fund reported 3.19M shares. Calvert owns 22,078 shares for 0.09% of their portfolio. Johnson Finance Group holds 28,155 shares or 0.5% of its portfolio. Duncker Streett And holds 1,518 shares. Nelson Van Denburg And Campbell Wealth Group Inc Incorporated Lc holds 0% of its portfolio in Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) for 43 shares. Caisse De Depot Et Placement Du Quebec holds 0.11% or 394,417 shares in its portfolio. Cibc Asset Mngmt reported 0.02% in Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC). 722 were reported by Mcf Advisors Lc. Brandywine Inv Ltd Liability Corp holds 311,608 shares or 0.21% of its portfolio. Acropolis Invest Mngmt Ltd Liability Com accumulated 6,367 shares. Piedmont Inv Advsrs holds 0% or 62,107 shares.
Since January 26, 2017, it had 0 insider buys, and 15 sales for $7.00 million activity. On Thursday, February 9 the insider STEWART MARTA R sold $317,976. The insider Galanko William Andrew sold 5,934 shares worth $706,917. $180,490 worth of Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) was sold by Hurlbut Thomas E. Shares for $119 were sold by BUSH WESLEY G. 34,417 Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) shares with value of $4.12M were sold by Squires James A. 1 Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) shares with value of $117 were sold by LOCKHART MICHAEL D.







Leuthold Group Llc increased its stake in Norfolk Southern Corp. (NSC) by 350.65% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Leuthold Group Llc bought 34,749 shares as the company’s stock declined 7.75% while stock markets rallied. The hedge fund held 44,659 shares of the railroads company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $4.83M, up from 9,910 at the end of the previous reported quarter. Leuthold Group Llc who had been investing in Norfolk Southern Corp. for a number of months, seems to be bullish on the $34.91 billion market cap company. The stock declined 2.07% or $2.55 reaching $120.71 on the news. About 1.32M shares traded. Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) has risen 34.32% since July 19, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 17.62% the S&P500.
Leuthold Group Llc, which manages about $1.60B and $893.92M US Long portfolio, decreased its stake in Usg Corp. (NYSE:USG) by 218,132 shares to 21,246 shares, valued at $614,000 in 2016Q4, according to the filing. It also reduced its holding in Universal Forest Products Inc. (NASDAQ:UFPI) by 44,824 shares in the quarter, leaving it with 5,735 shares, and cut its stake in Ishares Floating Rate Bond Etf (FLOT). 
More notable recent Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) news were published by: Gurufocus.com which released: “New England Research & Management, Inc. Buys Norfolk Southern Corp, Amgen Inc …” on July 11, 2017, also Nasdaq.com with their article: “Norfolk Southern Shares Cross 2% Yield Mark” published on July 06, 2017, Roanoke.com published: “Passenger rail service returns to Roanoke on Halloween” on July 18, 2017. More interesting news about Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) were released by: Pennrecord.com and their article: “Train dispatcher sues Norfolk Southern Corp.” published on July 18, 2017 as well as Reuters.com‘s news article titled: “BRIEF-Norfolk Southern to consolidate operating divisions” with publication date: July 18, 2017.
Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) Ratings Coverage
Among 24 analysts covering Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC), 5 have Buy rating, 5 Sell and 14 Hold. Therefore 21% are positive. Norfolk Southern Corp. had 53 analyst reports since July 28, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The firm has “Underweight” rating by Morgan Stanley given on Friday, June 3. As per Tuesday, July 28, the company rating was downgraded by Scotia Capital. As per Thursday, June 16, the company rating was initiated by Oppenheimer. Barclays Capital downgraded Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) rating on Monday, October 5. Barclays Capital has “Underweight” rating and $76 target. Topeka Capital Markets initiated Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) on Tuesday, August 11 with “Hold” rating. The rating was maintained by Cowen & Co with “Outperform” on Thursday, January 28. The company was downgraded on Friday, July 31 by Argus Research. As per Thursday, March 23, the company rating was downgraded by RBC Capital Markets. The stock of Norfolk Southern Corp. (NYSE:NSC) earned “Neutral” rating by Buckingham Research on Wednesday, January 18. The stock has “Hold” rating by Topeka Capital Markets on Wednesday, November 25.


